@node USAGE "So.....How do I use it then?"

How do I use it?
----------------

   Okay when you run the program it checks for all the files it needs, and
   will warn you then exit if any are missing :)

   Right now your at the main window you will see a String Gadget at the
   top, below are 2 Text gadgets, below that is a Listview, and finally at
   the bottom are 3 buttons.

   The String gadget is where you enter your code or areaname.
   
   The 2 text gadgets display codes in the top and place/area in the one
   below that.
   
   The Listview will display all the results of searches etc..

   The three buttons at the bottom are self-explanatory (The info button
   does not do anything yet!)

   Advanced info:

   If you enter part of a code, or the first so many letters of a place,
   all matches will be displayed.. for example

   example 1 ** :

   I Enter 017 in the string gadget AmPCS will search and display All codes
   that start 017 (eg 0171, 01776, 01732) and the associated places in the
   listview..

   example 2 ** :

   I enter DER in the string gadget, and all places that start DER (eg
   Derby, Derry) are displayed along with their codes in the listview!.

  Finally clicking on an entry in the listview will give all the details for
  that place in the 2 text gadgets above :)

@endnode

