@node CREATE "You want to Create a Codes file then?"

Okay there are 2 ways of creating a codes file.. the first is to use the
program MAKECODE (CLI/SHELL ONLY) and the required text file.. which looks
like this : (taken from english codes)

01246xxxxx?                           Chesterfield, Derbyshire
01247xxxxxx                           Bangor, Co. Down
012477xxx?                            Ballywalter, Co. Down                                    [Newtownards]
012477xxxxx                           Kircubbin, Co. Down
0124771xxx                            Kircubbin, Co. Down                                      [Newtownards]
0124772xxx?                           Portaferry, Co. Down                                     [Newtownards]
0124772xxxx                           Portaferry, Co. Down                                     [Newtownards]
0124773xxx                            Portavogie, Co. Down                                     [Newtownards]
0124774xxx                            Greyabbey, Co. Down                                      [Newtownards]

To simplify it:

Diallingcode + areacode (01246xxx)    Area Name, District name

so derby would be

01332xxxx                             Derby, Derbyshire

then simply run this through MAKECODE and it'll output it for you!!

Way 2 is:

The stdcodes.txt file is read by AmPCS it takes the following format:

Dialling Code
Area Code
Areaname, district name(s)

so derby would be :

01332
xxxx  (or blank line!!)
Derby, Derbyshire

and Stogumber would be:

01984
56
Stogumber, Somerset

..

There are a few points to remember

1). Dialling codes should not exceed 5 numbers (0171 or 01332)
2). Area Numbers should be upto 4 numbers
3). Area names and District names should be MAX 30 letters

@endnode
